- Greenhouse gas score is a rating that indicates the level of greenhouse gas emissions;
- Fuel economy score reflects the efficiency of a vehicle in terms of fuel consumption;
- City and highway fuel economy represent the average miles per gallon (MPG) a vehicle can achieve in urban and highway driving conditions.

- CO2 emissions are a significant contributor to greenhouse gas emissions and climate change;
- The query focuses on manufacturers with a substantial presence in the market, defined as having more than 10 vehicles in the dataset;
- The greenhouse gas score is an additional metric that provides insight into the environmental impact of the vehicles.

- "Tortoises of the road" refers to vehicles with lower fuel efficiency, symbolizing slow and steady consumption;
- "Combined fuel economy" is the average of city and highway fuel economy, typically measured in miles per gallon (MPG);
- "Born after 2010" refers to vehicles manufactured in the year 2011 or later.

